  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "nUYREDAw47Fvmp5XlMeEB/TBwP8=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## UX: Collaborate tab inside the Chat panel\n\n### Why the chat panel?\n\nThe chat panel already owns everything collab needs:\n\n- Peer address resolution.\n- Public profile lookup (Bee pubkey for ACT).\n- Multi-user picker patterns (from the existing document-share picker).\n- Notification plumbing.\n\nAdding Collaborate next to the existing conversation list keeps everything multi-peer in one place rather than scattering peer-oriented UI across the app.\n\n### Layout\n\n```\nChat Panel (left pane)\n  \u251c\u2500\u2500 [Conversations] tab    \u2190 existing\n  \u2514\u2500\u2500 [Collaborate]    tab   \u2190 NEW\n        \u251c\u2500\u2500 \"+ New collaboration\" button\n        \u251c\u2500\u2500 Pending invitations  (I received)\n        \u2514\u2500\u2500 Active collaborations (I'm part of)\n```\n\n### Key flows\n\n- **Create:** pick target (Drive or Document), pick participants (multi-select from known chat peers or paste a Swarm ID), optional caption, click Invite.\n- **Accept:** recipient sees a `CollabInviteCard` in chat \u2014 mirrors `DocumentShareCard` but with `[Join]` instead of `[Import]`.\n- **Active row:** drive/doc name, participant avatars (initials \u2014 allowed as a list, not a per-editor overlay), last activity timestamp. Click opens the drive/doc in Connect.\n- **Leave:** local-only stop (feed writes/pulls stop); initiator can later remove from manifest.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
    }
  },
